"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-news-world-france-trains-live-eurostar-olympic-games-arson-paris-opening-ceremony-b1173040.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"News|World  Eurostar and other French high-speed rail networks were thrown into chaos on Friday as a series of arson attacks disrupting travel to Paris only hours before the Olympic opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 241, \"end\": 249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.030545432782317e-13, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}, {\"begin\": 260, \"end\": 266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6690781520455295, \"rank\": 0.42726637477334534, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 375, \"end\": 380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prime Minister Gabriel Attal saying there would be \\\"massive and serious\\\" consequences both for people trying to travel to Paris and for those heading to other parts of the country or across the Channel.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 445, \"end\": 458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}, {\"begin\": 552, \"end\": 557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"National rail company SNCF said its Atlantic, North and East networks were damaged in the incidents, with fires laid across the tracks, while an attempted attack in the South-East was foiled.\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 656, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNCF\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"SNCF\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNCF\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNCF\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trains from London to Paris and Lille were being delayed by around an hour and a half, with a quarter cancelled.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999990595825, \"rank\": 9.35794945204132e-10, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 849, \"end\": 854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 859, \"end\": 864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999990287810929, \"rank\": 7.653778468418534e-07, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eurostar said this would remain the case over the weekend, with the service not back to normal until Monday.\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 1048, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 940, \"end\": 948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.030545432782317e-13, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All high-speed trains to and from Paris have been diverted to a slower line and the company urged customers to postpone their journeys if possible.\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1084, \"end\": 1089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prosecutors in Paris opened a national investigation, saying the crimes could carry sentences of 15 to 20 years.\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1311, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1214, \"end\": 1219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French rail operator SNCF said the situation should last \\\"at least all weekend\\\" but that teams were already on site carrying out checks and beginning repairs.\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1313, \"end\": 1319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6690781520455295, \"rank\": 0.42726637477334534, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1334, \"end\": 1338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNCF\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"SNCF\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNCF\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNCF\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Live updates  That's all for our live coverage on the disruption to Eurostar services.\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1543, \"end\": 1551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.030545432782317e-13, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please followour live coverage of the Paris Olympic opening ceremony here.\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1601, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics - one of the most-watched television events in the world with an estimated 1.5 billion people set to turn in from all corners of the globe - has started in Paris.\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1808, \"end\": 1813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers say the show will last for about three hours, though if history is any guide it will overrun.\", \"from\": 1816, \"to\": 1920, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All eyes are riveted on the giant screens set up along the Seine as competing nations travel up the river on boats.\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 2037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1981, \"end\": 1986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9940601990683904e-18, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Greece are first.\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2038, \"end\": 2044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999377165738361, \"rank\": 5.001474723305831e-05, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shots of soccer legend Zinedine Zidane appears on the screen to a round of applause.\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2080, \"end\": 2095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among other celebrities on the red carpet, onlookers have seen Vogue editor Anna Wintour and director Baz Luhrmann.\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2219, \"end\": 2231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Wintour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.893889695847768e-57, \"text\": \"Anna Wintour\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Wintour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Wintour\"}, {\"begin\": 2245, \"end\": 2257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baz_Luhrmann\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Baz Luhrmann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baz_Luhrmann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baz_Luhrmann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chrissy Teigen was with musician husband John Legend with their children Miles and Luna.\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2260, \"end\": 2274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chrissy_Teigen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chrissy Teigen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4610556\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chrissy_Teigen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chrissy_Teigen\"}, {\"begin\": 2301, \"end\": 2312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Legend\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John Legend\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Legend\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Legend\"}, {\"begin\": 2343, \"end\": 2347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3539391187206986e-24, \"text\": \"Luna\", \"types\": [\"Q634\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports fans have gone wild as actor Tom Hiddleston opened BBC One's coverage of Paris 2024 wandering around Paris and speaking to the camera looking smooth, charming and handsome.\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2386, \"end\": 2400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Hiddleston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Hiddleston\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Hiddleston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Hiddleston\"}, {\"begin\": 2408, \"end\": 2415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_One\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.884891294724764e-30, \"text\": \"BBC One\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_One\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_One\"}, {\"begin\": 2430, \"end\": 2440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.220828908140367e-27, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2458, \"end\": 2463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking in French, he announced: \\\"Let the Games begin.\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2543, \"end\": 2549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6690781520455295, \"rank\": 0.42726637477334534, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Welcome to Paris,\\\" before continuing in English: \\\"This is a story 100 years in the making.\\\"\", \"from\": 2587, \"to\": 2678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2598, \"end\": 2603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One said on X, formerly Twitter: \\\"Sheer class.\\\"\", \"from\": 2680, \"to\": 2727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French Prime Minister Gabriel Attal said attackers behind \\\"co-ordinated\\\" vandalism which caused disruption ahead of the Olympics had knowledge of the rail network and targeted the \\\"nerve centres\\\" of the system.\", \"from\": 2729, \"to\": 2939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2729, \"end\": 2750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Prime Minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2751, \"end\": 2764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What we know, what we see is that this operation was prepared, coordinated, that 'nerve centres' were targeted, which shows a form of knowledge of the network to know where to strike.\\\"\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 3126, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Attal added during a visit to the transport ministry crisis centre: \\\"I can not tell you more about the authors and their motivations.\", \"from\": 3128, \"to\": 3261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I see the impact, a massive impact for many of our fellow citizens.\", \"from\": 3262, \"to\": 3333, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB fan Ian Ralph said he felt \\\"panic\\\" and \\\"stressed\\\" when he realised his train to Paris was cancelled on Friday ahead of Olympics events his family have tickets for, including the women's football on Sunday and beach volleyball on Monday.\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3335, \"end\": 3342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9988839865673246, \"rank\": 0.0010991408953118077, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 3423, \"end\": 3428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking at St Pancras, the researcher from Southampton said: \\\"We looked straight on our phones, saw the headlines and then my wife got an email from Eurostar straight away going 'your train's been cancelled'.\\\"\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3791, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3625, \"end\": 3636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southampton\", \"score\": 0.9924839775562956, \"rank\": 0.0075729347929933775, \"text\": \"Southampton\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southampton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southampton\"}, {\"begin\": 3731, \"end\": 3739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.030545432782317e-13, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Ralph, 48, said he managed to book him and his family onto a train at 6pm - around three hours later than his original booking.\", \"from\": 3793, \"to\": 3923, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When asked how he felt when he saw the news, Mr Ralph said: \\\"Panic, but then you go into like 'okay, what do we need to do?'\\\"\", \"from\": 3925, \"to\": 4050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He continued: \\\"I am just stressed - I just want our train to come up on the board here and then we will get into the system, then I think I can relax once I know they are checking us in.\", \"from\": 4052, \"to\": 4238, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our girls are 12 and 14 - the next time the Olympics come to Europe they will be grown up, when it was in London they were babies - so this is our chance to go and do the Olympics with them.\\\"\", \"from\": 4240, \"to\": 4432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4347, \"end\": 4353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999990595825, \"rank\": 9.35794945204132e-10, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ariana Grande and Cynthia Erivo, the stars of the film Wicked, have made their way to Paris for the Olympic opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 4434, \"to\": 4559, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4434, \"end\": 4447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariana_Grande\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariana Grande\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariana_Grande\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariana_Grande\"}, {\"begin\": 4452, \"end\": 4465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cynthia_Erivo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cynthia Erivo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cynthia_Erivo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cynthia_Erivo\"}, {\"begin\": 4520, \"end\": 4525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Erivo wore green, Grande wore pink, and that's likely not a coincidence - given the color scheme of the story.\", \"from\": 4561, \"to\": 4671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The film is scheduled for a late November release.\", \"from\": 4672, \"to\": 4722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Carl Lewis, the US nine-time Olympic gold medalist in track and field, was among the long list of celebrities that hit the red carpet before the opening ceremony of the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 4724, \"to\": 4916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4735, \"end\": 4745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 4751, \"end\": 4753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.7354234513104451, \"rank\": 0.35975728691704173, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And even though he's more than 30 years removed from his third and final Olympics - Barcelona in 1992 - the legendary sprinter and jumper understands what athletes of this generation must be feeling on the brink of these Paris Games.\", \"from\": 4918, \"to\": 5151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am very emotional,\\\" Lewis told France 2 television during its broadcast.\", \"from\": 5153, \"to\": 5228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5176, \"end\": 5181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\", \"score\": 0.9369800901464301, \"rank\": 0.056399623296927735, \"text\": \"Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\"}, {\"begin\": 5187, \"end\": 5195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_2\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"France 2\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_2\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_2\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"First of all, I understand what these young people are going through and I appreciate the fact that they have come to a wonderful, beautiful country and a beautiful city.\", \"from\": 5229, \"to\": 5400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A lot of these athletes have never been to Paris or seen this energy before.\", \"from\": 5401, \"to\": 5477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5444, \"end\": 5449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8530135289246076e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, I think it's incredible.\\\"\", \"from\": 5478, \"to\": 5507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lady Gaga rehearsed for about an hour near the Austerlitz Bridge, a sign that the American pop star will perform at Friday's opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 5509, \"to\": 5651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5509, \"end\": 5518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 5591, \"end\": 5599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9529614612536638, \"rank\": 0.04936035627754604, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She finished up around 5.40pm, two hours before the ceremony was set to begin, and waved to fans as she walked off with her bandmembers.\", \"from\": 5653, \"to\": 5789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The area near the start of the Olympic parade route where she was singing features a makeshift yellow staircase in the traditional style of the old French subways, with an improvised subway sign simply but appropriately called PARIS.\", \"from\": 5791, \"to\": 6024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5939, \"end\": 5945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6690781520455295, \"rank\": 0.42726637477334534, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her representatives would not confirm to the Associated Press that she was performing.\", \"from\": 6026, \"to\": 6112, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6071, \"end\": 6087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9966807902664279, \"rank\": 0.003330263577303479, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spectators are rushing into the venue near Invalides after waiting for hours, initially told scanners at their entrance were broken.\", \"from\": 6114, \"to\": 6246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6157, \"end\": 6166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0330442653692143e-34, \"text\": \"Invalides\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It left a number of older spectators like 66-year-old Erica Chammas flustered and frustrated as many visitors pushed into her and a number of young children in line.\", \"from\": 6248, \"to\": 6413, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6302, \"end\": 6307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erica_Kane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.057215479407053e-17, \"text\": \"Erica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erica_Kane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erica_Kane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They were pushed through a cattle pen all through one door,\\\" the 66-year-old English-French woman said.\", \"from\": 6415, \"to\": 6519, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They way we were let in was shocking.\", \"from\": 6520, \"to\": 6558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The little girl next to me was nearly trampled.\\\"\", \"from\": 6559, \"to\": 6607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\", \"from\": 6609, \"to\": 7487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6669, \"end\": 6678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.9999999782003217, \"rank\": 2.09337379335323e-08, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 6769, \"end\": 6778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.